    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix get_single_ue_rnti() function to properly check for single UE\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_single_ue_rnti()` function in telnetsrv_bearer.c was not properly verifying that exactly one UE was connected before returning an RNTI. This could lead to incorrect behavior when multiple UEs were connected.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_bearer.c`: Modified `get_single_ue_rnti()` to count UEs and only return RNTI when exactly one UE is present\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_rrc.c`: Applied same fix to `get_single_ue_id()` function\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen multiple UEs are connected and commands like `get_single_rnti` are called via telnet interface, the function would previously return the RNTI of the first UE found in the tree traversal rather than properly returning -1 to indicate multiple UEs are present. This could lead to incorrect bearer operations being performed on the wrong UE.\n\nThe error message \"different number of UEs\" suggests the function should verify there's exactly one UE, but the original implementation did not enforce this constraint.\n"
}